folder: Humboldt Street & Scholes Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Humboldt Street, west side, north from Scholes Street. Scholes Street, is in the foreground. October 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing new buildings erected under the Federal Housing Act. July 23, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Scholes Street & Humboldt Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:

folder: Scholes Street & Humboldt Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)

195-201 Scholes Street, north side, east from Humboldt Street. Also seen is Humboldt Street, east side, north from Scholes Street.

October 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

The same; as seen from west of Humboldt Street, showing the site after clearance for a Federal housing project. The buildings in the right background are on Bushwick Ave; the steeples at the left, are on St. Margaret's Hospital.

December 22, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Scholes Street & Humboldt Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Scholes Street, north side, between Humboldt Street (left) and Bushwick Ave. (right). These buildings were later demolished (1935) to make way for Federal low rental apartments. September 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
